// Details for: soundcore-q30-headphones (Soundcore Life Q30, model A3028)
// Lab sheet: CV-EB-A3028-001 — §7.5 ELEVATED gold deepen (Wave Adj/Mid product 7/8).
//   Upgraded from the first protocol-grade bench (~148 lines) that already held
//   Timer+ AAC ANC OFF/ON stopwatches, Kkmoon weight, FNB58 charge, BT walk,
//   Transport/Indoor/Outdoor app verification, and Egypt field ANC notes. This
//   pass adds sibling A/B ladder hygiene vs Q20i / Space One / Q45, hard-case
//   vs soft-pouch trade, airline cabin note, and speech-band honesty — WITHOUT
//   inventing new dB / ms / SNR and WITHOUT pasting sibling stopwatch rows as
//   this sample's own numbers.
//   Any vendor "% noise reduction" / dB figure = vendor-stated only (§11.3 / §14).
// Wave headphones (over-ear). Physics envelope enforced (§8). §7.5 adapted for
//   over-ear / on-ear: A = full-unit weight (+ hard case); B = playtime ANC OFF
//   + ANC ON; C/E case steps = N/A (no charging case); D/F = USB-C full + quick
//   charge on the unit; G = BT range; H = multipoint; I = ANC qualitative only
//   (no anechoic / no invented dB); J = mic qualitative (no SNR); K = codecs in
//   Soundcore App; L = latency qualitative (no ms).
// Sibling ladder: Q11i (A3005, no ANC) → Life Q20 / Q20i (A3004, hybrid ANC +
//   soft pouch) → Life Q30 (A3028, Transport/Indoor/Outdoor + hard case, this
//   file) → Space One (A3035, Adaptive ANC + LDAC + soft pouch) → Space Q45
//   (A3040, Adaptive ANC + LDAC + hard case). Sibling files intentionally untouched.
// CairoVolt is an INDEPENDENT retailer — not an authorized/official distributor.
// Engineer sign-off: Eng. Omar Khaled · testDate 2026-07-24 · sample CV-EB-A3028-001.
